1
00:00:00,080 --> 00:00:05,773
QualCanvas offers several analysis views, but the tool should follow the question.

2
00:00:05,773 --> 00:00:10,517
Decide whether you need to inspect language, coding patterns, cases

3
00:00:10,517 --> 00:00:14,312
or a developing framework before opening a chart.

4
00:00:14,712 --> 00:00:19,905
The Analyze menu separates text exploration from coding analysis and comparative frameworks.

5
00:00:19,905 --> 00:00:24,233
That structure helps you choose a method instead of clicking

6
00:00:24,233 --> 00:00:28,560
every output and keeping only the one that looks persuasive.

7
00:00:28,960 --> 00:00:34,074
The dashboard is useful for checking coverage, code distribution and project progress.

8
00:00:34,074 --> 00:00:38,336
Uneven counts may reveal a sampling issue, a code that

9
00:00:38,336 --> 00:00:42,598
is too broad or simply a concept that appears less

10
00:00:42,598 --> 00:00:43,024
often.

11
00:00:43,424 --> 00:00:47,258
Co-occurrence shows codes that overlap in passages.

12
00:00:47,258 --> 00:00:53,283
Coding queries let you combine conditions with and, or and not.

13
00:00:53,283 --> 00:00:58,760
Neither establishes causation; both help you find material worth rereading.

14
00:00:59,160 --> 00:01:03,136
Analysis nodes live on the same canvas as the source material.

15
00:01:03,136 --> 00:01:06,750
Position a result near the relevant codes, then write a

16
00:01:06,750 --> 00:01:10,364
memo that records what you think it means and what

17
00:01:10,364 --> 00:01:11,448
could contradict it.

18
00:01:11,848 --> 00:01:17,821
Before reporting a frequency or matrix, inspect the code definitions and examples.

19
00:01:17,821 --> 00:01:22,799
If coders used a label inconsistently, refine or recode before

20
00:01:22,799 --> 00:01:25,288
treating the result as stable.

21
00:01:25,688 --> 00:01:31,291
The strongest analysis loop is question, inspect, reread, memo and challenge.

22
00:01:31,291 --> 00:01:36,384
Use the visual outputs to locate evidence, then make the

23
00:01:36,384 --> 00:01:39,440
argument in your own analytical voice.
